The paper discusses a network-layer architecture against DDoS attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The approach also involves dynamic server IP address change, which relates to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and system integration (cs.SI). The paper also mentions modules necessary to implement the approach, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE).
